#: ../../../whatsnew/3.16.rst:92
msgid ""
":func:`gzip.open` now accepts an optional argument ``mtime`` which is passed "
"on to the constructor of the :class:`~gzip.GzipFile` class. (Contributed by "
"Marin Misur in :gh:`91372`.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../whatsnew/3.16.rst:97
msgid "lzma"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../whatsnew/3.16.rst:99
msgid ""
"Add support of new BCJ filters ARM64 and RISC-V via :const:`!lzma."
"FILTER_ARM64` and :const:`!lzma.FILTER_RISCV`.  Note that the new filters "
"will work only if runtime library supports them. ARM64 filter requires "
"``lzma`` 5.4.0 or newer while RISC-V requires 5.6.0 or newer. (Contributed "
"by Chien Wong in :gh:`115988`.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../whatsnew/3.16.rst:106 ../../../whatsnew/3.16.rst:200
msgid "logging"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../whatsnew/3.16.rst:108
msgid ""
":class:`~logging.handlers.TimedRotatingFileHandler` now uses the creation "
"time instead of the last modification time of an existing log file as the "
"basis for the first rotation after handler creation, if supported by the OS "
"and file system. This allows it to be used in short-running programs that "
"start and end before the rotation interval expires. (Contributed by Iv├Īn "
"M├Īrton and Serhiy Storchaka in :gh:`84649`.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../whatsnew/3.16.rst:117
msgid "math"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../whatsnew/3.16.rst:119
msgid ""
"Added trigonometric functions that work in units of half turns, rather than "
"radians. The new functions :func:`math.acospi`, :func:`math.asinpi`, :func:"
"`math.atanpi`, and :func:`math.atan2pi` return half-turn angles. The new "
"functions :func:`math.cospi`, :func:`math.sinpi`, and :func:`math.tanpi` "
"take half-turn angle arguments. These functions are recommended by IEEE "
"754-2019 and standardized in C23. (Contributed by Jeff Epler in :gh:"
"`150534`.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../whatsnew/3.16.rst:128
msgid "os"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../whatsnew/3.16.rst:130
msgid ""
"Add :func:`os.pidfd_getfd` for duplicating a file descriptor from another "
"process via a pidfd.  Available on Linux 5.6+. (Contributed by Maurycy "
"Paw┼éowski-Wiero┼äski in :gh:`149464`.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../whatsnew/3.16.rst:135
msgid "shlex"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../whatsnew/3.16.rst:137
msgid ""
"Add keyword-only parameter *force* to :func:`shlex.quote` to force quoting a "
"string, even if it is already safe for a shell without being quoted. "
"(Contributed by Jay Berry in :gh:`148846`.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../whatsnew/3.16.rst:142
msgid "xml"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../whatsnew/3.16.rst:144
msgid ""
"Add support for multiple multi-byte encodings in the :mod:`XML parser <xml."
"parsers.expat>`: \"cp932\", \"cp949\", \"cp950\", \"Big5\",\"EUC-JP\", "
"\"GB2312\", \"GBK\", \"johab\", and \"Shift_JIS\". Add partial support (only "
"BMP characters) for multi-byte encodings \"Big5-HKSCS\", \"EUC_JIS-2004\", "
"\"EUC_JISX0213\", \"Shift_JIS-2004\", \"Shift_JISX0213\", \"utf-8-sig\" and "
"non-standard aliases like \"UTF8\" (without hyphen). The parser now raises :"
"exc:`ValueError` for known unsupported multi-byte encodings such us "
"\"ISO-2022-JP\" or \"raw-unicode-escape\" instead of failing later, when "
"encounter non-ASCII data. (Contributed by Serhiy Storchaka in :gh:`62259`.)"
msgstr ""

